This exhilarating experiences takes adventurous holidaymakers near the summit of the tallest peak in the world without having to endure the treacherous climb – all for £3m a ticket.

But anyone who goes on this hot air balloon ride must have a head for heights – in addition to deep pockets – as they float over Mount Everest and the Himalayas at an eye-watering altitude of more than 30,000ft.

For those who can afford it, the once-in-a-lifetime ride is well worth it, boasting a stunning 360-degree view of snow-topped mountains like they have never been seen before.

